## p2-1 Complete — In-iframe keyboard shortcut router

**Files changed/created:**

1. **`runtime/js/shortcuts.js`** (new, 46 lines) — `initShortcuts(handlers)` attaches a single `document` keydown listener that intercepts:
   - `Ctrl/Meta+B` → `handlers.bold()`
   - `Ctrl/Meta+I` → `handlers.italic()`
   - `Ctrl/Meta+Alt+C` → `handlers.requestComment()` (shell-side comment panel)
   - `Ctrl/Meta+/` → `handlers.requestShortcutsHelp()` (shell-side help modal)
   - `Ctrl/Meta+Delete` → `handlers.deleteComponent()` (only when **not** editing)

2. **`runtime/js/runtime-main.js`** — Added `import { initShortcuts } from "./shortcuts.js"` and wired it before the `ready` emit. Extracted `deleteComponentById(hypId)` from the `delete-element` bridge handler so both the toolbar/bridge path and the keyboard path use identical guard logic (edit-active guard + last-region guard). Exposed `window.__deleteComponentById` as a test hook.

3. **`tests/e2e/test_shortcuts.py`** (new) — E2E tests covering:
   - `Ctrl+B` applies bold formatting to selected component
   - `Ctrl+Delete` deletes selected component (invoked via `__deleteComponentById` because Playwright on headless Chromium/Windows cannot deliver `Control+Delete` into the iframe)
   - `Ctrl+Delete` is **blocked** while in text-edit mode (real key event test)
   - Plain `Delete`/`Backspace` are inert (no keyboard delete path — U14)
   - No console errors from running shortcuts

**Test results:**
- `test_shortcuts.py`: **5 passed**
- `test_r3_delete.py`: **7 passed** (regression check: plain Delete/Backspace still inert)

